    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "synchronicity feels too much like a coincidence. it wasnt just a coincidence. when i looked at that vase, i didnt just 'feel' something, i actually saw the shimmer of the explosion in the reflections of the cracks. it was like a preview. and it happens all the time with other things too. how can you just call it a coincidence when it's this specific? it feels like i'm seeing the timeline before it actually happens.",
